<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-06-06T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-06-06T11:00:00-05:00" n="650" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d650">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">693.003/564: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-06-06T12:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">June 6,
                                            1919, noon.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>Your May 28, 8 p.m.</p>
                            <p>Draft of Revised Import Tariff received with Arnold’s letter of
                                December 18, 1918,<note n="83" xml:id="d650fn83">Not printed; for
                                    the rules in question, see <ref target="#pg_663">pp.
                                        663</ref>–<ref target="#pg_664">664</ref>.</note> had three
                                rules on page numbered 39 pasted to draft, and sheet of additions
                                and corrections pasted on inside front cover. No rules or additions
                                and corrections with copies of Tariff received with Arnold’s letter
                                April 3. Advise whether those sent with letter December 18 were
                                final and whether they and the Draft of Tariff were agreed to by
                                delegates of foreign nations.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>